    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-13T22:00:00-03:00"
                            >July 13, 1932—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 13—8:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reliable information received in São Paulo that movement in Minas Geraes led by
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAS1">Arthur Bernardes</persName> has deposed
                        <persName>Olegario Maciel</persName> and is favorable to São Paulo. This is
                    decisive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
